headline: A Republican Confident That Trump ‘Will Still Be a Player’
text: WASHINGTON — For all the drama around the presidential race, the biggest surprise of the 2020 election may have been in the House, as Republicans gained seats and cut into the Democratic majority after a campaign in which officials in both parties expected the G.O.P. to lose seats.
snippet: The California Republican believes his party’s victories in 2020 came thanks to the president, not in spite of him: “He brought turnout.”
